CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper December 14, 1957, pg. A3, reads: "Polio Leaders - Among those attending the testimonial dinner, honoring the leadership of the Allegheny County polio vaccine program, at Webster Hall, Monday evening, were, left to right: Mrs. Leo P. Sheehy, Mrs. Joseph Salk, Dr. Jonas Salk of the University of Pittsburgh and discoverer of the polio vaccine, and Basil O'Connor, president of the National Foundation for Infantile Paralysis. The dinner was sponsored by the local chapter of the latter organization. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Unknown man, Mrs. Leo P. Sheehy, Donna Lindsay Salk, Dr. Jonas Salk, and Basil O'Connor at testimonial dinner for Allegheny County polio vaccine program, Webster Hall
